pageContext.claim: “We’ve accomplished historic amounts in a short period of time. We’ve signed more than 50 pieces of legislation. They said we’ve signed none — none....You ever hear of these liars back there, where they say, but Trump hasn't gotten -- I think we've gotten more in a short period of time, in this seven months, I think we've gotten more than anybody, including Harry Truman, who was number one, but they will tell you we've got none.”
pageContext.analysis: We highly doubt any news organization has reported that Trump has signed no legislation. But it is often noted that Trump, unlike many presidents in their 7th month, has signed no major legislation. When Trump made his remarks, he has signed 54 bills, most of which were minor. Just among recent presidents, Jimmy Carter, George H.W. Bush and Bill Clinton had signed more bills than Trump at this point in their presidencies.
